Sentencas: Among different designs of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs), bi-electrode supported cells (BSC) offer great prospects for superior specific power density due to low weight and volume.
Titulo: BaZr0.9Yb0.1O3-δ-modified hi-electrode supported solid oxide fuel cells with enhanced coking and sulfur tolerance

Sentencas: This BSC architecture is used as a platform for an anode surface modification study to increase the anode's coking and sulfur poisoning resistance when operating under common hydrocarbon-containing fuels.
Titulo: BaZr0.9Yb0.1O3-δ-modified hi-electrode supported solid oxide fuel cells with enhanced coking and sulfur tolerance

Sentencas: Here we report a Ni anode modified by BaZr0.9Yb0.1O3-delta particles that demonstrates stable performance in CH4 (without coking) and decreased sulfur poisoning.
Titulo: BaZr0.9Yb0.1O3-δ-modified hi-electrode supported solid oxide fuel cells with enhanced coking and sulfur tolerance

Sentencas: The anode was fabricated by infiltrating Ni precursor into a porous YSZ scaffold in combination with small amounts of Ba, Zr, and Yb nitrates.
Titulo: BaZr0.9Yb0.1O3-δ-modified hi-electrode supported solid oxide fuel cells with enhanced coking and sulfur tolerance

Sentencas: The electrochemical performances of the modified anodes were compared with blank Ni anodes infiltrated in the same manner.
Titulo: BaZr0.9Yb0.1O3-δ-modified hi-electrode supported solid oxide fuel cells with enhanced coking and sulfur tolerance

Sentencas: In addition, the structure, morphology, and phase composition of the anodes were studied using X-ray diffraction, microscopy, and Raman spectroscopy.
Titulo: BaZr0.9Yb0.1O3-δ-modified hi-electrode supported solid oxide fuel cells with enhanced coking and sulfur tolerance
